exercises.name: Squats
exercises.description: Squats train all leg muscles: glutes, quadriceps, inner thighs, and lower back.
tips: Do not arch your back. Keep your pelvis back. As you rise up, make a powerful push upward.
instructions: 1. Place your feet shoulder-width apart, keep your hands along your body, knees slightly bent, back flat.
2. Squat untill your thighs are parallel to the floor and body leaning forward and pelvis pulled back.
commonMistakes: Squatting too low or too high. Incorrect positioning.

exercises.name: Jumping Jack
exercises.description: Enter a dynamic, full-body aerobic exercise improving cardiovascular endurance and coordination
tips: Focus on landing softly and keeping your movements controlled. Keep your breathing rhythmic and controlled throughout the exercise. If you're new to jumping jacks, start with a lower number of reps and gradually work your way up.
instructions: 1. Stand upright with your feet together and your arms at your sides.
2. Jump your feet out to the sides while simultaneously raising your arms above your head.
3. Your hands should meet above your head as your feet land on the floor.
4. Jump your feet back together and lower your arms to the starting position.
commonMistakes: Not landing softly. Letting your knees cave in. Allowing your shoulders to hunch. Not engaging your core.

exercises.name: Lunges
exercises.description: The exercise is considered one of the most effective and useful exercises for pumping the gluteal muscles.
tips: Tilt your torso straight back. Tense your abs. Do not squeeze your buttocks.
instructions: 1. Stand up straight, legs slightly apart so that the foot, knee, thigh, and shoulders form a straight line.
2. Step forward and transfer weight to the front leg, hips and shins of both legs to form a right angle.
3. Then push the heel off the floor and using the gluteus and rear thigh muscles, return to the starting position.
commonMistakes: Swinging from side to side. Incomplete amplitude.

exercises.name: Walk Down to Plank
exercises.description: This exercise strengthens and tightens your stomach, abs, posture, arms, and legs, burning a lot of calories.
tips: Hold the plank pose for a few seconds. Do the exercise at your optimal pace.
instructions: 1. Stand up straight and bend forward smoothly.
2. Then use your hands to reach a straight plank position.
3. Return to the starting position.

exercises.name: Down Box
exercises.description: The exercise engages almost all major muscle groups and is a great addition to the previous exercises.
tips: Twist your abs during the punch. Squat until your hips are parallel to the floor.
instructions: 1. Start in a squat position.
2. Stand up and shift your weight to one leg and strike with the opposite arm.
3. Then do the same and kick with the another arm.
commonMistakes: Squatting too low or too high. Small kick amplitude.

exercises.name: Elbow Cat Cow Pose
exercises.description: This exercise is great for warming up and stretching your spine, shoulders, and neck, so take your time and focus on moving mindfully through the poses.
tips: Make sure your elbows are directly under your shoulders and your knees are directly under your hips to maintain a stable base. If you have any pain or discomfort in your wrists or forearms, you can place a blanket or yoga block under your elbows for support.
instructions: 1. Begin on your hands and knees with your wrists directly under your shoulders and your knees directly under your hips.
2. Lower down onto your forearms so that your elbows are directly under your shoulders.
3. Take a deep breath in and arch your back, dropping your belly towards the floor and lifting your tailbone towards the ceiling.
4. As you exhale, round your spine upwards, tucking your chin towards your chest and drawing your navel towards your spine.
5. When you're finished, release the pose and come back into your hands and knees.
